HEADWORD: Rapport
<hw>Rap*port"</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧p*p⟦omac⟧rt"; F. r⟦adot⟧`p⟦ocir⟧r")</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. <ets>rapporter</ets> to bring again or back,
to refer; pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>apporter</ets> to bring, L.
<ets>apportare</ets>. Cf. <er>Report</er>.]</ety> <def>Relation;
proportion; conformity; correspondence; accord.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T is obvious what <qex>rapport</qex> there is between the
conceptions and languages in every country.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Temple.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs>\'d8<col><b>En` rap`port"</b></col> <pr>(⟦aum⟧N`
r⟦adot⟧`p⟦ocir⟧r")</pr> <ety>[F.]</ety>, <cd>in accord, harmony, or
sympathy; having a mutual, especially a private, understanding; in
hypnotism, in that relation of sympathy which permits influence or
communication.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rapprochement</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
